This paper discusses the security and privacy concerns related to network function outsourcing to the cloud, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a framework for secure service function chaining, which involves the management and orchestration of network functions in the cloud, making it relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), and systems and control (cs.SY).
